		<item>
			<title>Activity - Pictures with Sound Search</title>
			<link>https://culturall1.idrc.ocadu.ca/index.php?option=com_content__view=article__id=108__catid=17__Itemid=53</link>
			<description><![CDATA[<p align="left">The <a href="http://www.mccord-museum.qc.ca/scripts/explore.php?Lang=1__tableid=4__tablename=department__elementid=00016__true" target="_blank">Notman Photographic Archives</a> at the McCord Museum&nbsp;includes&nbsp;an on-line collection of over 80,000 photographs. </p><p align="left">As part of the Culturall project, over 11,000 images were matched with background sounds in order to investigate the usefulness and feasibility of providing sound effect based accessible multimedia equivalents on a large scale. A customized ambient sound is create for each image by mixing background sounds appropriate to the various elements in each image. </p><p align="left">In order to allow public access to this resource, the McCord has created a &quot;pictures with sound search&quot; option that lets visitors search by each of the background sounds.</p><ul><li><div align="left"><a href="http://www.mccord-museum.qc.ca/scripts/sound_search.php?Lang=1" target="_blank">English Search Page</a></div></li><li><div align="left"><a href="http://www.musee-mccord.qc.ca/scripts/sound_search.php?Lang=2" target="_blank">French Search Page</a></div></li></ul>]]></description>
			<category>Modal Translation</category>
			<pubDate>Mon, 02 Apr 2007 10:41:42 +0000</pubDate>
		</item>
		<item>
			<title>Activity - &quot;Echophotograph&quot; Game</title>
			<link>https://culturall1.idrc.ocadu.ca/index.php?option=com_content__view=article__id=107__catid=17__Itemid=53</link>
			<description><![CDATA[<p align="left">The&nbsp;&quot;Echophotograph&quot; game is a multimodal activity in which the player attempts to determine which of four possible scenes matches a soundscape. The player does this by exploring the images and noting consistenceies or inconsistencies between the image and sound effects that are triggered as they explore.</p><p align="left">The game was made more accessible by the addition of keyboard navigation and zooming.&nbsp;</p><ul><li><div align="left">French Version (<a href="http://www.musee-mccord.qc.ca/fr/clefs/jeux/34" target="_blank">Part 1</a>, <a href="http://www.musee-mccord.qc.ca/fr/clefs/jeux/35" target="_blank">Part 2</a>)</div></li><li><div align="left">English&nbsp;Version (<a href="http://www.mccord-museum.qc.ca/en/keys/games/34" target="_blank">Part 1</a>, <a href="http://www.mccord-museum.qc.ca/en/keys/games/35" target="_blank">Part 2</a>)</div></li></ul>]]></description>
